# gdm is the session launcher: it is wired up (gdm user/group, PAM,
# custom.conf with WaylandEnable + automatic login of `user`, and a
# wayland-sessions/gnome.desktop), so let the vendor default enable it. Presets
# are reapplied on every boot here (volatile /etc, empty machine-id). GNOME does
# not use the tty1-autologin -> user compositor path (that is the weston image's
# model, in system-runtime-files-weston); gdm owns seat0 here instead.
#
# The diagnostic ttyS1 root console (diag-console.service) is enabled for every
# image from the base system-runtime-files, so it is not repeated here.
